Heroes
and Myths
The Trojan War
The Ancient Greeks told many stories about the Trojan
War, but today we are unsure of what is fact and what
is fiction. The stories tell of the ten-year siege of Troy,
and its eventual fall following a clever trick involving a
huge, hollow, wooden horse.
